## Tailwind CSS â€“ Introduction

**Tailwind CSS** is a utility-first CSS framework that lets you build modern, responsive designs directly in your HTML using pre-defined classes. Instead of writing custom CSS, you compose styles by combining small utility classes, making development faster and more consistent.

### âœ¨ Features
- Utility-first workflow
- Fully responsive design support
- Highly customizable
- Small production build size
- No runtime dependency

### âš¡ How It Works
Tailwind scans your project files for class names, generates only the required styles, and outputs a static CSS file. This keeps your final CSS lightweight and optimized.

### ğŸ“¦ Use Cases
- Web apps
